<TITLE> 4 die after mistaking pesticide for sugar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)Four day labourers died in Sirajganj after consuming what they believed was a packet of sugar on Tuesday, but turned out to be pesticide, officials said. The deceased were identified as Abdullah, 60, Abul Kashem, 16, Farid Uddin, 23, and Bulbuli Khatun, 45, from Digholkandi Gosaibari village in Chouhali upazila. The four died on the spot while another labourer, Rabiul, 40, was taken to hospital after falling ill, Sheikh Abdur Razzaque, police chief of Enayetpur thana, under Chouhali, told bdnews24.com. Razzaque, quoting Rabiul, said that the labourers while working in a field found a polythene packet containing a white substance that looked like sugar. "They ate it sprinkled on bread at lunch, fell immediately sick and died," said the police officer. "Locals managed to rescue Rabiul in time to send him to the hospital," Razzaque said. The substance was examined at the hospital. "We found that it was a granular organo-phosphate compound, a pesticide," Mohammad Masum, duty doctor at Khaza Younus Ali Medical College, told bdnews24.com. Rabiul was recovering, Dr Masum added. bdnews24.
